text.text:
Amazing Rajasthan typical food.

The restaurant is just 2min from Chand Baori Stepwell attraction. The staff were very friendly and welcoming.

Mainly Vegetarian but also Vegan friendly.

All the dishes we had were delicious. Very well prepared and presented, with lots of herbs and interesting flavors.

We definitely recommend this place!

text.text: Hello! We came there for lunch and ordered sweet lassi, Dal Tadka (with lentils), Palak Paneer (with spinach) and butter roti (bread). We asked non-spicy and finally for the first time the food was truly non-spicy and we enjoyed the taste of every ingredient. Lassi so far was the best one here. The dishes are extremely tasty, we were so happy for our lunch. The place is family-owned and very well-curated, you perceive cozy atmosphere of a countryside and relax in a peaceful environment. Strongly recommend this place, thank you!

text.text: Just 5 minutes walk from the stepwell this hotel is an oasis - lovely gardens, a swimming pool (a little murky but still great to swim in) and beautiful rooms. Not much choice on the menu and the electricity and water occasionally goes off, but worth it to stay in such a lovely place. We visited as part of an Intrepid tour, my favourite hotel of the trip.

text.text:
The property is just opposite to Chand Baori.
It's a very quiet place.
The staff are always smiling and ready to prepare your meals.

We got the opportunity to be hosted by the owner  Mr.K.K. Singh. His warmth and hospitality show through all his actions throughout our stay.

The rooms were very spacious.  The furniture and decor were very tastefully done.
The food was very homely and tasty.
We enjoyed camp fire and star gazing too.
Can't forget to mention the company of the peacocks, peahens and squirrels!
